statements.sql:
select count(*) as aggregate from (select `weight`.`id`, `scale_name`, `provinces`.`name` as `province_name`, `customers`.`name` as `customer_name`, `minrals`.`minral_name`, `second_weight`, `mineral_net_weight`, CASE WHEN weight.discharge_place = "Process" THEN SUM(weight.mineral_net_weight) * 10
WHEN weight.discharge_place = "Checked" THEN COUNT(weight.id) * 200 END AS weighing_total, CASE WHEN weight.discharge_place <> "Process" AND weight.discharge_place <> "Checked" THEN (weight.mineral_net_weight * purchase.unit_price) END AS royality, `discharge_place`, `vehicles_id`, `date` from `weight` left join `minrals` on `weight`.`mineral_id` = `minrals`.`id` left join `purchase` on `weight`.`purchase_id` = `purchase`.`id` left join `customers` on `purchase`.`customer_id` = `customers`.`id` left join `afg_map_info` on `weight`.`scale_id` = `afg_map_info`.`scale_id` left join `provinces` on `afg_map_info`.`province_id` = `provinces`.`id` where `date` between '' and '' group by `weight`.`id`, `scale_name`, `provinces`.`name`, `purchase`.`unit_price`, `customers`.`name`, `minrals`.`minral_name`, `second_weight`, `mineral_net_weight`, `discharge_place`, `vehicles_id`, `date`) as `aggregate_table`
